FACE: Turn toward a direction or person

Syntax: face <direction>
        face <person>
        face clear
        face

DESCRIPTION:
  Sets your visible position string so the room list shows which way
  you are turned. Example:

    face north
    (room shows: You faces north.)

    face sal
    (room shows: You faces Sal.)

  Directions include north, south, east, west, up, down, and the
  diagonal and in/out variants.

  Type face alone to see your current facing. face clear resets it.
  Moving to a new room also clears your facing.

SEE ALSO: position, look
